76561198024972696,Recommended,304410,33734392,Posted: 22 July,all,DALCOhstangultion,"""Hexcells Infinite"" continues the upward trend of the already great ""Hexcells"" line of games.  This game differs from the previous game in that it now includes a puzzle generator and the ability to save the progress of a game.  So, once finished with its 36 built in puzzles, you can play an infinite number of generated puzzles (hence the name), and when you get brain-fatigue in the middle of a big puzzle, you can quit without losing your progress.  As with ""Hexcells Plus,"" ""Infinite"" jumps right in and ramps right up.  The game is excellent and all puzzles are solvable without guessing.  The save ability is especially useful because some of these puzzles are huge (puzzle 6-8 took me about 3 hours to complete).  My only real complaint is that some of the puzzles are still too big (even though they can be saved).  With exception of completing 60 randomly generated puzzles to get the final Achievement, finishing the game with all the rest of the Achievements took 19.8 hours.  So, again, it's a game well worth the money.For those who don't believe all the puzzles can be solved without guessing, I refer you to a guide which proves it:https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=373284523"
