,Recommended,304410,13300978,"Posted: 9 December, 2014",all,Shioame,"--Revised Review--So, after getting some other replies commenting that I wasn't giving fair review to the game, I've decided to give  another shot before revising the review. I brewed some coffee, have some nice cookies on plate. Clicked the game, headphones on, play time.Things that I noticed, is that this game is incredibly logical. Horsemedic (guy who commented) was right, this game is entirely made out of logic, to the point of ridiculousness.One of the rule, ""-#- means that blue numbers of panels are NOT connected"", sounds quite simple, but when you think about it, this phrase DID NOT say ""ALL blue panels are NOT connected"". Which means, there is at least one panel that isn't next to each other, but has no guarantee in -3- as this can have 3 blue panels that are not connected, or have pair that is next each to other and have one separated. While this only make the game confusing, it still is, following the rule of the game.Further that I played, I noticed that this ""hole"" of the rule isn't conflicting the game at all. If you get stuck, you can look for other clues. Eventually you'll hit the spot you were stuck on, but with more clues to help out.I've already said in the last review but the graphic and music are top notch. I like the color use of this game, it's gentle and comfortable to see it for long time. Music is very relaxing, good soothing sound.I guess, the only complain that I can make at this point is that I wish there were spread sheet of set of rules instead of explaining it beliefly and let you try it out during the gameplay. (which helps too but isn't very clear sometime) As understanding the set of rules become the most crucial part of this game I think developer could have spent a little more time for it. Maybe, on the first Hexcell, it might have been more user friendly. I haven't tried it yet.As a last note, this is NOT a minesweeper. Who ever said it is, did not think enough through like me. The format is very close to it, I agree, but the minesweeper somtime takes you to a gamble while Hexcell can make ""educated guess"" to clear without making single mistake.So let me say it again- this game, is NOT a minesweeper. It is more like a Sudoku. Don't expect be like one; this game has no timer, nor any score system for it. Take your time. Grab coffee or tea. Rewind your brain and take the challenge.I recommend this game."
