,Recommended,304410,33655576,Posted: 19 July,all,Solamandar,"First time giving a shot for an English review.K, if you are looking for a good puzzle game. Dah, right place for ya.Hexcell series is very (not) brain-friendly, and I absolutely love it.The ""Infinite"" mode, as I saw in some other reviews, appears to be repeative. And it is.Here is a quick answer for those who are bothered by this problem.These ""random"" stages, as you can see on the generating page, are generated from a certain seed.If you don't understand what this seed stands for, don't bother. Just FYI, a certain seed can only generate one certain pattern of Hexcell puzzle. This explains why you sometimes see repeated puzzles. Well, I guess the one you see most times is the one generated by those zeroes, lol.Anyway, I am not able to explain the algorithm how a Hexcell puzzle is generated from a seed. But you still have 10^8, which is eight hundred million, puzzles to enjoy in total (they may not be as challenging tho). So I believe it is worth having this interesting game collected in your library."
