76561198028973936,Recommended,304410,14276427,"Posted: 1 February, 2015",all,Zolphia,"Hexcells is one of my favourite puzzle games in recent years. It is similar to minesweeper, but with an important difference: there is no guesswork, everything can be worked out entirely through logic. So if you ever feel stuck, you know it is not due to poor puzzle design, but because you simply haven't reasoned your way through the next step yet.There was one small downside to the previous Hexcells games, which is that it didn't remember how far along a puzzle you were when you quit the game. And since some of the later, more complicated puzzles can easily take more than half an hour to figure out, it is a welcome addition to Hexcells Infinite that it now stores your intermediate progress within a puzzle.If this type of logic puzzle appeals to you, I highly recommend getting the Complete pack containing all three Hexcells games for the full experience."
