76561197970345570,Recommended,304410,20591044,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,rockhopper,"The third version of this game, following Hexcells and Hexcells plus.Again the basic puzzles are a bit harder than with plus and a LOT harder compared to the first Hexcells.Where plus gave us additional new rules for the puzzles, this sequel doesn't do that. It only perfects the difficulty of what the previous parts had to offer.But why the name ""infinity""? It comes with a Random Puzzle Generator, offering no less than 100.000.000 puzzles. This is where the true replay value shines. Want to share a certain puzzle with a friend? Just give the puzzle grid number to him and he can load it no problem. You can even save a puzzle midway, Something that is lacking in the standard puzzles.All in all a very valuable addition to an already great game.As with the previous two parts, ALL puzzles can be solved by using simple (and sometimes not so simple) logic. You never have to guess to solve something there's always a ""if this needs this, then that must be so or so"". Highly recommended if you enjoyed the previous parts. If you found 'plus' too hard, the random puzzles are a bit less difficult sitting somewhere between the original and plus."
