,Recommended,304410,27975260,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,KaiKat,"I can wholeheartedly recommend this game to anyone & everyone including those that may not know how to play Minesweeper style games.The Hexcells games involves a much improved and varied Minesweeper style gameplay compared to the standard Minesweeper clones that are nearly everywhere (including the standard Minesweeper installed on most Windows computers).Hexcells improve on the basic Minesweeper format in quite a number of different ways that change up the Minesweeper gameplay by adding different alternative ways on locating the mines. I won't spoil the fun of working them out for you though.Speaking about the new and different ways of locating the mines, the main campaign of pre-defined set levels slowly introduce these new mechanics to players while explaining the methods you can use these to solve the puzzles. This starts with the basics so that even a novice easily start to play and goes all the way up to some really challenging tests towards the end with the final puzzle taking hours to complete. Luckily this game auto saves constantly so you can ways come back to where you left off.Hexcells Infinite is probably the best of out the 3 current Hexcells games due to the new Infinite mode (that wasn't in the previous 2 games) which randomly generates new levels so there's always something to come back to or continue on after the main campaign is completed.As you can see in the screenshots on this store page it has a nice minimalist look with both light & dark setting so that you're not blinded by that white blackground all the time.It runs very well on any PC that I've had no matter the specs low or high. Variety of resolution settings which all seem to work great and a nice window mode setting so you can play while doing something else (like watching a movie or TV show, etc).The only improvement I could think of was if the Infinite mode had some more generation settings so you can generate a puzzle more to your liking rather then it being nearly completely random.9.5/10"
